Tad Tadlock https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tad_Tadlock 0 Thelma "Tad" Tadlock (January 19, 1931 – December 8, 2000) was a dancer and choreographer known for her work in television, Broadway theater and movies, including starring in the General Motors sponsored-film shorts "Design for Dreaming" (1956) and "A Touch of Magic" (1961).
